### The previous version in which this bug was not present was

Before Vite

### Description

When I try to add .html in a route as described below, then that route is not available through `ng serve`. However, if I replace `.html` with something else, like `.asd`, then the page loads correctly.

### Minimal Reproduction

```sh
ng new repro-app #  (select CSS in dialog and say no to SSR)
cd repro-app
ng g c repro-page
```

Fill `app.routes.ts` like so:

```ts
import { Routes } from '@angular/router';
import { ReproPageComponent } from './repro-page/repro-page.component';

export const routes: Routes = [
    {path: 'test.html', component: ReproPageComponent},
    {path: 'test.asd', component: ReproPageComponent},
    {path: 'test', component: ReproPageComponent}
];
```

After that, execute

```sh
npm run start
```

Then, if you
- go to localhost:4200/test.html => You get **Cannot GET /en/search.html**
- go to localhost:4200/test.asd => You get **repro-page works!**
- go to localhost:4200/test => You get **repro-page works!**

